response.original_title: Tony Law: A Law Undo His-elf What Welcome
response.overview: In A Law Undo His-elf What Welcome, Tony Law is closer than ever to nonsense nirvana. Behold the comedy event horizon. Without a hint of a joke, this powerful show has achieved a sort of comedy which aims at making no sense at all and yet, and yet, and yet it means everything. Every dog damned thing ever. Science called and they want their goal back. Law has burst the net. You will feel sick with awe. You will barf wonder.  This show is a code. The words are all jumbled up but when you put them in the right order the wormhole opens up. Nothing is the same anymore. You can't call this comedy. This isn't comedy… It's something else... It's ...OTHER. Anthony Johnston Law
response.tagline: This isn't comedy… It's something else... It's ...OTHER.
